========,1,preface.
Seward Township is a township in Nobles County, Minnesota, United States.
The population was 259 at the 2000 census.
========,2,Geography.
According to the United States Census Bureau, the township has a total area of 35.7 square miles (92.6 km²), of which 35.7 square miles (92.3 km²) of it is land and 0.1 square miles (0.2 km²) of it (0.25%) is water.
Jack Creek and the south fork of Jack Creek are like a spider web on the map of Seward Township.
The creek touches no fewer than twenty of the thirty-six sections of land within the township.
